other_tests.findings: There is no intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. The extrahepatic common duct is mildly dilated up to 7 mm, with no stones visualized. The gallbladder is full with a mildly thickened wall and contains numerous shadowing stones. No evidence for intramural edema or pericholecystic fluid. Possible hypoechoic lesion noted, but may be artifactual.
